# A hypothetical `npm pack` ships exactly: package.json, index.d.ts, and the
# built auto_node.node addon. Everything Rust stays out — the package is a
# binary artifact + its hand-written types, not a compile-on-install source
# distribution (no prebuilds in v0; the addon is built on and for the build
# host — see evals/embedded-node/README.md). The package is private: true;
# this file exists so the boundary is explicit, not because v0 publishes.
src/
tests/
build.rs
Cargo.toml
